## 5. Install Git in Ubuntu

Steps to install Git:

1. Update package list:
   sudo apt update

2. Install Git:
   sudo apt install git

3. Verify installation:
   git --version

---

## 6. Create a Project Locally and Push to GitHub

Step 1: Create a project directory
mkdir myproject
cd myproject

Step 2: Initialize Git repository
git init

Step 3: Create a file
echo "Hello Git" > file.txt

Step 4: Add file to staging area
git add file.txt

Step 5: Commit changes
git commit -m "Initial commit"

Step 6: Connect to GitHub repository
git remote add origin [https://github.com/username/repository.git](https://github.com/username/repository.git)

Step 7: Push code to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

---

## 7. Create a Project in GitHub and Clone to Local

Step 1: Create repository in GitHub

* Click “New Repository”
* Enter repository name
* Click “Create Repository”

Step 2: Clone repository to local system
git clone [https://github.com/username/repository.git](https://github.com/username/repository.git)

Step 3: Move into project directory
cd repository

Step 4: Add files
echo "My Notes" > notes.txt

Step 5: Commit and push changes
git add .
git commit -m "Added notes"
git push

